def get_page(c_time,c_url):
    # 
    url = f'https://games.mobileapi.hupu.com/1/8.0.65/bplcommentapi/bpl/comment/list?publishTime={c_time}&order=desc&outBizNo={c_url}&outBizType=games_series&clientCode='
    response = requests.get(url=url).json()
    # 
    info = []
    for i in response['data']['comments']:
        commentId = i['commentKey']['commentId']
        commentUserId = i['commentUserId']
        publishTime = i['publishTime']
        commentUserName = i['commentUserName']
        commentDate = i['commentDate']
        ipLocation = i['ipLocation']
        commentContent = i['commentContent']
        score = i['score']
        info.append([commentId, commentUserId, publishTime, commentUserName, commentDate, ipLocation, commentContent, score])

    # 
    next_publishTime = response['data']['cursor']['publishTime']

    return next_publishTime, info

def save_info(name, character_info):
    # 
    csv_file_path = f"YuanShenData/{name}.csv"
    with open(csv_file_path, mode='a', newline='',encoding='utf-8') as file:
        writer = csv.writer(file)
        writer.writerows(character_info)

def auto(name,c_time,c_url,num):
    # 
    n = 1
    if num == 0:
        num = 5
    else:
        num = num // 10
    while n <= num:
        character_info = get_page(c_time,c_url)
        # 
        save_info(name,character_info[1])
        # 
        c_time = character_info[0]
        print(f'Successfully:{name},{10*n}')
        # 
        time.sleep(random.random())
        n = n + 1

def comment_content_stat():
    # 
    comment_content = []
    for i in data['commentContent']:
        comment_content.append(i)

    comment_content_cloud = ' '.join(comment_content)

    # 
    mask = np.array(Image.open("other/yuanshi.png"))
    wordcloud = WordCloud(font_path="other/font.ttf", background_color='white', mode="RGBA", mask=mask)
    wordcloud.generate(comment_content_cloud)
    plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5),dpi=300)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

    pd.DataFrame(comment_content).value_counts().to_csv('data/comment_content.csv',header=None)
    comment_content = pd.read_csv('data/comment_content.csv',header=None)
    comment_content.columns = ['comment', 'count']
    # print(comment_content)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6),dpi=300)
    plt.bar(comment_content.head(25)['comment'],comment_content.head(25)['count'],color='#476479')
    plt.rcParams['font.sans-serif'] = ['SimHei']
    plt.xticks(rotation=90,fontsize=8)
    plt.title('')
    plt.xlabel('')
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.show()

def long_comment_stats():
    long_comment_content = []
    long_comment_score = []
    for i in range(len(data)):
        if len(data.iloc[i]['commentContent']) > 200:
            long_comment_content.append(data.iloc[i]['commentContent'])
            long_comment_score.append(data.iloc[i]['score'])
    long_comment = pd.DataFrame(long_comment_content,long_comment_score)
    sample_long = long_comment.sample(10)
    print(sample_long[0])

long_comment_stats()
